FBIS4-60139 "drnes099_n_94004" FBIS-NES-94-099 Daily Report 21 May 1994 LEBANON Reaction to al-Dirani Seizure Reported Reaction to al-Dirani Seizure Reported Arad Said `Sold' to Iranian Guards NC2105085894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0830 GMT 21 May 94 NC2105085894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South Arabic BFN [Text] Our political correspondent reports that Mustafa al-Dirani sold Israeli navigator Ron Arad to the Iranian Revolutionary Guards for $300,000 in 1989. REUTER cites Husayn al-Musawi [Islamic Amal Movement leader] as saying that the abduction of al-Haj Mustafa al-Dirani will not make them deviate from the course of struggle against the Israeli enemy.
